-- U.S. Senate clears way for Burwell's health secretary confirmation
-- By David Morgan
-- Wed Jun 04, 2014 12:20PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, June 4 (Reuters) - The U.S. Senate on Wednesday cleared the way for lawmakers to decide on Thursday whether to confirm Sylvia Mathews Burwell as President Barack Obama's new health secretary.   (Reporting by David Morgan; Editing by Doina Chiacu)  ((david.morgan@thomsonreuters.com)(+1)(202)(898 8326)(twitter.com/dmorganreuters)(Reuters Messaging: david.morgan.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: USA HEALTHCARE/BURWELL

